<Author>stevie51
<Content>Lovely Little Hotel Stayed 'All Inclusive' at the CBM the last two weeks in June2008. We arrived at the hotel mid afternoon and was met by the Manager and given a refreshing fruit drink while we registered. We were given a room upgrade and found ourselves in a room overlooking the pool and beach.(room 123). The first thing is to praise every member of staff, I have never met such a happy and pleasant group of genuine people, and not for the hope of tips all the time. If you introduce yourself to them, they don't forget and call you by name all the time.The room was spotlessly clean and had clean towels every day and the bedding was changed on a regular basis, although the towels were getting a little on the thin side.The food was an average buffet on most nights but there was always plenty of variety. Breakfast was always worth getting out of bed for, eggs cooked as you want while you wait, decent crispy bacon, fruit, cooked meats, cheese, and other oriental foods.On Thursday nights there is a Mongolian BBQ which is taken outside by the poolside bar, this was excellent and shouldn't be missed. You also have access to the Chinese Restaurant 'Chopsticks' which is next to the Reception Bar area, the only problem with that is, that if you are on all inclusive you only have a fixed menu, not 'al a carte'. A tip for the chinese is to go in when you arrive and ask to see the fixed menus for the week and book a table for a night that has the menu you most favour. Its well worth a visit.While we were there, there was always plenty of sunbeds both around the pool and on the beach and no shortage of beach towels. If you are around the pool there is always afternoon entertainment and Volleyball on the beach at 4.00pm daily.On the beach there are hawkers selling locally made goods, but once told you are not interested they don't pester you.Also on the beach is the watersports office and can be quite busy with jetskis and paragliding etc. this is all booked through 'Bruno' who can also arrange a taxi for the day for you. Don't pay the first price he asks, if you are willing to barter he will reduce the price. We had a taxi for a full day and paid the equivilent of 拢25.00 and the driver takes you where ever you like.There is also a free shuttle bus that leaves the hotel at 17 mins past every hour and takes you to a local shopping mall which is quite nice.A word of warning if you are walking outside the hotel, beware of the man on the motor bike touting for 'time share'. Its the usual thing, open a ticket, win a prize, attend a presentation and win wonderful gifts. This all takes in excess of 4 hours and isn't worth it.The sea is not the best if you enjoy swimming in the sea, its not very deep, and quite weedy.Dont forget your US$25 per person entry visa payable on arrival and departure tax of 150,000 Rupiah per person. 
