<Content>Accept the cultural differences of the guests first ! First of all you have to mention the staff here - they are superb, and nothing is too much of a problem. Congratulations to all of them has to be mentioned. and they are the saving grace at this hotel. I stayed here for 2 weeks and have to say the hotel could be quiet, and offers itself to French tourists in the main who can be noisy and unwittingly annoying. Spoiling on a daily basis the calm that could be appreciated if they didnt clog the bar, get drunk ( one drink seems to do it ) and continuously flout the pool side regulations. And on one occasion this did result in a very violent confrontation between these guests and others. Not a holiday memorable moment. They cater for large groups who do take over the small bar area ( which isnt 24 hrs - it shuts at midnight ) And there is little escape from them if quiet is your requirement. That aside its a nice place to stay, on the beach affording a great view of the ocean and very cheap taxi's to Kuta, which is a must for clubbers and good dining enthusiasts alike.Look out for the illegal money changer opposite the hotel, they operate with little aggression but can do magic tricks with your money only Paul Daniels could worlk out. For those who dont appreciate average buffet food the retsuarants locally are a must, and very cheap. Bumba Bali is a must visit. And for $ 6 you can get shoes made in 24 hrs that fit superbly as they are made to measure. There are many advantages to outweigh the arrogance of some fellow guests.Overall great staff, average food, and if your lucky little noise, although I would guess that is not going to happen too often.Would I stay here again ? No - the reasons are stated here, would I reccomend this hotel - yes - but beware of the potential for others with little or no manners spoiling your quiet time. 
